latestPosts.caption:
Japan, Spring Break 2025 🇯🇵🏯🗾. We weren’t sure if our boys were too young to enjoy Japan, and it ended up being one of our most favorite family trips. My faves below ⬇️ and lots of kid friendly tips.

Kyoto: we stayed @ritzcarltonkyoto which was a perfect blend of Japanese architecture, hospitality, and the best French bakery outside of France @pierrehermeofficial 
- Bike Tour through Historic Kyoto: Shaan was on a tandem bike which kept him busy and independent, without me being terrified of him plowing into a crowd of pedestrians. Jay @cyclekyoto was the best guide. 
- Fushimi Inari Taisha Shrime: We avoided temple fatigue by picking one that we could hike through. Keeping the boys moving was key to fighting jet lag and avoiding meltdowns. 
- Traditional Ramen and Gyoza Making Class: we always take a cooking class with a local chef when we travel, it’s the perfect way to learn about the culture while keeping the kids engaged.
- Nishiki Market: I was worried this would be a bunch of fake LV hawkers like the markets in Marrakesh and Istanbul, but not at all! So charming and full of culinary surprises.
- Cherry Blossoms at Niko Castle: Spectacular catching the sunset and light show here. 
- Restaurants: Musoshin, Hiro Beef Kyoto, Velrosier, Monk 

Tokyo: we stayed @fstokyo , the hotel bar Vertu is reason enough to stay here. 
- Culinary Tour through Asakusa: it’s a lot of eating in Japan, but calories don’t count on vacay. 
- TeamLab Planets: I was willing to get over my germaphobia to do this. 
- Sunshine City: This is basically Vegas for kids with claw machines, arcade games, and Pokeman for days. 
- Mipig Cafe: You get to hang with baby pigs. Period.
- Sumo Stables: definitely go to the training stables instead of a match, it’s fascinating to see these giant humans wrestle up close. They even offered to have us join them for breakfast post their training session. We politely declined, sumo bod is not on the summer moodboard. 
- Restaurants: Roppongi Inakaya Higashiten, Ukai Tei, Tonkatsu Narikura
Good vibes only #revolvefestival #coachella. Tagged and links in bio!
